# =============================================================================
# Debian Bookworm (12.15) CVE suppressions
# All 19 findings lack available fixes in the stable repos as of 2026-07-13.
# OS-level CVEs will auto-resolve when Debian publishes point-release updates.
# Review quarterly: apt-get upgrade output will show which are fixed.
# No Node.js CVEs are suppressed — after npm@11 upgrade and lockfile removal,
# the rebased image scans 0 Node.js vulnerabilities.
# =============================================================================

# --- CRITICAL ---

# CVE-2023-45853  zlib1g (will_not_fix)
# Vulnerable MiniZip code path is NOT built into Debian's zlib1g package.
# Confirmed "ignored" in Debian security tracker. Safe to suppress.
# https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2023-45853
CVE-2023-45853

# CVE-2026-42496  perl-base (fix_deferred)
# Archive::Tar symlink traversal. Debian postponed until upstream regression
# issues are resolved. Not exploitable without direct untrusted archive
# processing in the application — this image serves HTTP API, not tar files.
# https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42496
CVE-2026-42496

# CVE-2026-8376  perl-base (affected)
# Heap buffer overflow in regex compilation, affects 32-bit builds only.
# This image is amd64 (64-bit). Not exploitable.
# https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-8376
CVE-2026-8376

# --- HIGH ---

# CVE-2026-53615  bsdutils / libblkid1 / libmount1 / libsmartcols1 / libuuid1 /
#                 mount / util-linux / util-linux-extra (affected)
# Integer overflow in libblkid's DOS partition parser. Requires physical or
# emulated volume access to exploit. Not reachable in this application.
# https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-53615
CVE-2026-53615

# CVE-2026-41992  gzip (fix_deferred)
# Global buffer overflow in LZH decompression. Exploitable only if attackers
# can supply crafted LZH-compressed input to gzip. The image does not run
# gzip on untrusted data.
# https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-41992
CVE-2026-41992

# CVE-2026-54369  libacl1 (fix_deferred)
# Symlink traversal privilege escalation via libacl functions. Requires local
# access to exploit. The image runs as non-root (USER node) with minimal
# filesystem access.
# https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-54369
CVE-2026-54369

# CVE-2025-69720  libtinfo6 / ncurses-base / ncurses-bin (affected)
# Buffer overflow in ncurses. Requires local terminal interaction to exploit.
# The image runs as a headless HTTP server — no terminal access.
# https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2025-69720
CVE-2025-69720

# CVE-2026-42497  perl-base (fix_deferred)
# Archive::Tar hardlink file modification. Companion to CVE-2026-42496.
# Not exploitable without direct archive extraction in the application.
# https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42497
CVE-2026-42497

# CVE-2026-48962  perl-base (affected)
# IO-Compress arbitrary code execution via attacker-controlled output glob.
# Requires Perl IO-Compress operations on untrusted data. Perl is present in
# the base image but is not used by the Node.js application at runtime.
# https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-48962
CVE-2026-48962

# CVE-2026-9538  perl-base (fix_deferred)
# Archive::Tar DoS via crafted tar header with large entry size. Companion
# to CVE-2026-42496 / CVE-2026-42497. Same rationale: not exploitable
# without direct archive processing in the application.
# https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-9538
CVE-2026-9538
